<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-11T13:43:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-11T13:43:00-05:00" n="686" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d686">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5804</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-11T18:00:00-00:43">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8.28 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Legation reliably informed that President of Liberia has received
                                from British Consul General a private note couched in terms
                                calculated to force Liberia to fix and publish date not later than
                                14th for deportation of Germans.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>